<h2><%= @fund_grant %></h2>

<p>FundSource: <%= @fund_grant.fund_grant.fund_source %></p>
<p>Status: <%= @fund_grant.status %></p>
<p>FundGrantor total: <%= number_to_currency @fund_grant.fund_editions.where( :perspective => 'requestor').sum('fund_editions.amount') %></p>
<% if permitted_to?( :review, @fund_grant ) || @fund_grant.released? -%>
<p>Reviewer total: <%= number_to_currency @fund_grant.fund_editions.where( :perspective => 'reviewer').sum('fund_editions.amount') %></p>
<p>Allocation total (after caps): <%= number_to_currency @fund_grant.fund_items.sum('fund_items.amount') %></p>
<table>
  <thead>
  <tr>
    <th>Category</th>
    <th>Allocation (after caps)</th>
  </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
  <% @fund_grant.fund_grant.fund_source.structure.categories.each do |category| -%>
  <% table_row_tag do -%>
    <td><%= category.name %></td>
    <td><%= number_to_currency @fund_grant.fund_items.allocation_for_category(category) %></td>
  <% end -%>
  <% end -%>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p>Note: Higher priority fund_items are allocated before lower priorities until the allocation cap is reached.</p>
<% end -%>

<% if @fund_grant.status == 'started' %>
<p>
Below is a listing of fund_items in your fund_grant.  You may add, move (re-prioritize),
and delete fund_items.  For each fund_item, you should also add requestor fund_edition specifiying
details about that fund_item, including the amount you are fund_granting.
</p>

<p>
When you are finished, instruct the appropriate officers of your organization to
approve this fund_grant.  After the fund_grant is approved, you cannot change it.
</p>
<% elsif @fund_grant.status == 'completed' %>
<p>
This fund_grant is now frozen because it has been approved by one or more authorized officers.
Its status will advance to <em>submitted</em> once all required approvals are
registered.
</p>
<% else %>
<% if permitted_to? :review -%>
<% if @fund_grant.status == 'accepted' -%>
<p>
This fund_grant is accepted for review by the commission.
</p>
<% end -%>
<% else -%>
<p>
This fund_grant is now submitted for review.
</p>
<% end -%>
<% end -%>

<h3>FundItems</h3>

<%= render :partial => 'fund_items/detailed', :collection => @fund_grant.fund_items.root,
  :locals => { :level => 4 } %>

<% unless @fund_grant.users.unfulfilled(Approver.where( :quantity => nil )).length == 0 -%>
<h2>Who must approve</h2>
<p>The following users must approve before the fund_grant may be considered submitted.</p>
<ul>
  <% @fund_grant.users.unfulfilled(Approver.where( :quantity => nil )).each do |user| -%>
  <li><%=h user %></li>
  <% end -%>
</ul>

<% end -%>
<% if @fund_grant.fund_grant.organization.registrations.current -%>
<h3>Membership information for <%=h @fund_grant.fund_grant.organization %></h3>
<dl>
<%= render :partial => 'registrations/membership', :object => @fund_grant.fund_grant.organization.registrations.current %>
</dl>

<% end -%>
<h3>Who has approved</h3>

<%= render :partial => 'approvals/approvals', :object => @fund_grant.approvals.includes(:user).all,
           :locals => { :user => true, :approvable => false } %>

<p>
<%= link_to h("Back to #{@fund_grant.fund_grant.organization}"), @fund_grant.fund_grant.organization %> |
<%= link_to h("Back to #{@fund_grant.fund_grant.organization} profile"), profile_organization_path(@fund_grant.fund_grant.organization) %> |
<%= link_to "Manage fund_items", fund_grant_fund_items_path(@fund_grant) %> |
<%= link_to 'Edit', edit_fund_grant_path(@fund_grant) %>
</p>

